'''Christopher Téa Opéri''' (born 29 April 1997) is an Ivorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for {{Turkish football updater|İstanbul Başakşehir}} club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Club career==
After years in the youth academy of [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]], Opéri was transferred to [[LB Châteauroux|Châteauroux]] on 24 July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maligue2.fr/2017/07/24/officiel-christopher-operi-sengage-a-chateauroux/|title=Officiel : Christopher Operi s'engage à Châteauroux – MaLigue2|date=24 July 2017|publisher=|access-date=10 October 2017|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603093243/https://maligue2.fr/2017/07/24/officiel-christopher-operi-sengage-a-chateauroux/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his first professional appearance with Châteauroux in a 2–1 [[Ligue 2]] loss to [[Gazélec Ajaccio]] on 22 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/83280|title=LFP.fr – Ligue de Football Professionnel – Domino's Ligue 2 – Saison 2017/2018 – 9ème journée – Gazélec FC Ajaccio / Châteauroux|website=lfp.fr}}</ref>

On 2 June 2021, he signed a two-year contract with [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] in Belgium.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]]|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/02-06-2021/bienvenue-christopher?|title=Bienvenue Christopher!|date=2 June 2021|access-date=13 October 2021|language=nl}}</ref> On 21 June 2022, Opéri's contract with Gent was terminated by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Gent|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/21-06-2022/osman-bukari-en-christopher-operi-verlaten-de-club|title=OSMAN BUKARI EN CHRISTOPHER OPERI VERLATEN DE CLUB|date=21 June 2022|access-date=21 June 2022|language=nl}}</ref>

On 29 June 2022, Opéri returned to France and signed a two-year contract with [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Le Havre|url=http://www.hac-foot.com/actualite/christopher-operi-s-engage-avec-le-havre-athletic-club.html|title=Christopher Opéri s'engage avec le Havre Athletic Club|date=29 June 2022|access-date=11 July 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

On 7 January 2025,  {{Turkish football updater|İstanbul Başakşehir}} club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] signed Opéri for 3.5 years.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 January 2025 |title=HOŞ GELDİN CHRISTOPHER OPERI |url=https://ibfk.com.tr/haberler/hos-geldin-christopher-operi |publisher=İstanbul Başakşehir F.K. |language=TR}}</ref>

==International career==
Opéri made his debut for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]] on 7 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group F|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]] at the [[Amadou Gon Coulibaly Stadium]]. He substituted [[Ghislain Konan]] in the 86th minute of a 1–0 Ivory Coast victory.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687265|title=Ivory Coast v Gabon game report|date=7 June 2024}}</ref>

Opéri was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |lang=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |lang=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d’Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Opéri was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Personal life==
Opéri was born in the Ivory Coast to an Ivorian father and French mother, and moved to France at a young age. His uncle [[Cyril Domoraud]] is a former professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linfodrome.com/sport/89398-christopher-operi-defenseur-du-havre-ac-etre-a-la-hauteur-en-selection-ivoirienne-je-n-ai-pas-de-doutes|title=Christopher Operi (défenseur du Havre AC) : " Etre à la hauteur en sélection ivoirienne ? Je n'ai pas de doutes "|first=Alex K.|last=PAYNE|date=16 August 2023|website=www.linfodrome.com}}</ref>

